To guys who could not launch the game - check carefuly what 'UMD ISO MODE' and 'CPU CLOCK GAME' you are using. At fist i was also thinking it wasn't so important, but then game proved me wrong. Try setting 'UMD ISO MODE' to 'M33 driver', and 'CPU CLOCK GAME' to 'Default' as shown on this screenshot:
http://img842.imageshack.us/img842/3627/20101027005604.png
At least that worked for me and dozens other people. Good luck.

I HAVE PATCHED THE GAME FOR PROMETHEUS 2 and 3 DOING THISâ€¦..

1:download isotool 1.81
2:put the isotool folder into game folder on psp
3:put the game in the iso folder on psp
4:start isotool and go to WWE 2011 iso press x
5:select eboot decrypt
6:it will ask u if you want a backup, say no
7:it will  ask you if you want to enable version patch say yes
8:It will then ask you if you want to start, say yes
9:When finished select the iso again
10:select patch
11:select prometheus
12:select 06BETA1 and press x
13:it will ask if you want to start say yes
14:when finished exit iso tool
15:go to vsh menu set CPU speed to 222 and change UMD driver to M33 then exit vsh menu
16: Start game.
